<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 2em;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
        .page-info {
            background: #f0f8ff;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            padding: 1em;
            margin: 1em 0;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        @page {
            size: <%= pageSize %>;
            margin: 1in;
        }
        @media print {
            body {
                margin: 0;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1><%= title %></h1>

    <div class="page-info">
        <h2>CSS @page Size Testing</h2>
        <p><strong>Page Size:</strong> <%= pageSize %></p>
        <p>This page uses CSS @page directive to set the page size.</p>
        <code>@page { size: <%= pageSize %>; }</code>
    </div>

    <div class="page-info">
        <h2>Common Page Sizes</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>A4:</strong> 210mm × 297mm (8.27" × 11.69")</li>
            <li><strong>Letter:</strong> 8.5" × 11" (215.9mm × 279.4mm)</li>
            <li><strong>Legal:</strong> 8.5" × 14" (215.9mm × 355.6mm)</li>
            <li><strong>A3:</strong> 297mm × 420mm (11.69" × 16.54")</li>
            <li><strong>A5:</strong> 148mm × 210mm (5.83" × 8.27")</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="page-info">
        <h2>Testing Notes</h2>
        <p>Use this page to test:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>CSS @page size directives</li>
            <li>How Printeer handles different page sizes</li>
            <li>Whether the specified page size is applied correctly</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Expected behavior:</strong> The generated PDF should use the specified page size: <strong><%= pageSize %></strong></p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>